Package: SingleBench
Type: Package
Title: Framework for benchmarking and optimising dimension-reduction and clustering pipelines in expression data analysis
Version: 1.0
Date: 2020-10-09
Author: David Novak
Maintainer: David Novak <davidnovakcz@hotmail.com>
Imports: magrittr, dplyr, purrr, ggplot2, scales, stringr, pheatmap, iterators, matrixStats, foreach, parallel, progress, RANN, RColorBrewer, rhdf5, SummarizedExperiment, HDCytoData, crayon, clusterSim, FlowSOM, Rphenograph, flexclust, uwot, Rtsne, clue, dimRed, coRanking, scattermore, flowCore, doParallel, caret, reshape, gtable, kableExtra, grid, gridExtra, cowplot, Rcpp, aricode
Suggests: reticulate, ivis, destiny
Description: SingleBench provides an extensible framework for applying dimension-reduction, clustering tools and combinations thereof to single-cell data. SingleBench is built to allow for rapid design of pipelines to benchmark methods and find optimal parameters, easy addition of new method wrappers and straightforward production of graphical reports.
License: MIT
